Bowl #42 : Yew 

Still buzzing from the #northbristolartstrail this past wkend. All the #52weeks52bowls project so far was on display, including a few sneak previews such as this yew bowl which managed to come 4th in the public vote. 

Yew is a very poisionous tree and as a general rule I won't be turning it too often*, however rules will be broken, and suffice to say I will wear a mask when doing so. I did feel a little weird when turning this, I presume due to the fine dust, and so improvised a face-mask using an old dishcloth and some string. Not exactly a fashion statement 🤣. 

(*I would do it as a commission, or maybe when I finally make a bow!) 

It is also a very beautiful tree, that has a striking light coloured sapwood and orangey centre, sometimes with streaks of purple in it. This log had been around for a while and had started cracking through the bark, which seems to happen often wih yew in my experience, and these cracks run deep! However from previous yew experience these cracks do tend to be quite strong, and despite overlapping cracks all the way to the bottom of this bowl it feels fairly stable when flexed (although I wouldn't like to drop it). 

These cracks and the general concern over the toxicity of the wood mean that it is not suitable for your soup! 🤪 It is however, very beautiful and full of interest as an object!

Haii #UpstreaMate, ada kabar baik dari Pertamina EP Jambi Field lohh😍

Pertamina EP (PEP) Jambi Field yang termasuk dalam Zona 1 Regional Sumatera Subholding Upstream Pertamina berhasil melaksanakan pengeboran dan menambah produksi minyak melalui sumur step out PPS-G yang berada di Desa Kasang Lopak Alai, Kec. Kumpeh Ulu, Kab. Muaro Jambi, Jambi. 

Sumur ini mulai ditajak pada 9 Oktober 2022 menggunakan rig PDSI #42.3/N-1500E, hingga mencapai kedalaman akhir TD 2109 mMD / 1899 mSSTVD. Pengeboran sumur PPS-G merupakan bagian dari ruang lingkup POD Lapangan Puspa Asri di PEP Jambi Field, yang termasuk dalam Subholding Upstream Pertamina, Regional Sumatera, Zona 1.

General Manager Zona 1, Muzwir Wiratama, menjelaskan bahwa sumur PPS-G ini menyasar Formasi Air Benakat Lapisan R#1. “Saat ini telah dilakukan uji produksi sejak 13 November 2022 dengan hasil laju produksi awal (Qoi) sebesar 522 barel per hari (Barrels Oil Per Day/BOPD) atau 348% dari target Qoi sebesar 150 BOPD. Sumur tersebut berproduksi secara natural flow dengan choke 7 mm, dengan laju produksi stabil sebesar 495 BOPD,” ujar Wira. 

Regional Sumatera Zona 1 berupaya memenuhi target produksi tahun 2022 yaitu minyak 22.817 BOPD dan gas 185 juta standar kaki kubik per hari (MMSCFD). Target ini dicapai dengan rencana kerja 27 sumur pengembangan, 3 sumur eksplorasi, 7 sumur workover dan tambahan khusus 6 sumur fracturing untuk ekselerasi peningkatan produksi, serta melakukan well services-well intervention sebanyak 934 sumur.

Mohon doa dan dukungannya ya #upstreaMate, semoga apa yang kami lakukan dapat berdampak positif bagi masyarakat luas. 😊🙏❤️

Chapter #42

Ashi's pov

I and avu are in the kitchen probably cleaning up the mess we made while preparing dinner and breakfast.

I can see the boys entering and and taking steps near us. Siddharth slides his hand around my waist and turned me facing him while riyaz did the same with Avu who was standing beside me.

They pulled is us closer and... stopped, while we were definitely thinking for something else to happen...
*Twin telepathy*
"Do you know how beautiful you are?" Both the boys asked their girls.
"Well, we'de know if you tell us..." Avu replied.
Siddharth moved more nearer to me and so did riyaz to avu.
"You've made a big mistake wifey and sis of teasing us." Sid said taking heavy breaths in.
"It may prove wronge baby girls." Riyaz said in the same way.
"Well, we find wronge things the most right ones I guess." I said while wrapping my arms around sid's neck, avu did the same.
"Then let us do wronge things baby." Sid said this and as soon as he finished the boys were about to kiss us and we were smiling bright wanting to enter the kiss but something that didn't meant to happen, that happened.

Sid's phone rings*

"Ughhh...I am gonna kill whoever it is, ruining the most beautiful moments." Siddharth said grinning. He picked up the call.
"Yeah, Siddharth here. What? But we are on leave we can't come right now...is it really important abhi? Okay, we'll be there in few minutes."

What!! No.

They can't go right now.

Not today atleast.

"Riyaz there's an emergency in the office, we need to hit there." Sid said Gazing riyaz.
"I won't come is it okay?" He asked
"Riyaz I can understand, I mean who wants to leave this beautiful views of the gorgeous ladies but work really needs us!" He stated sadly.
"Okay I hate it sometimes."
"It's okay boys, work is also important." Avu stated convincing.
"Yeah, I mean we have still 7 days on pack so...that's fine." I agreed.
"We'll be right back honey, wait for us." Siddharth said while placing a kiss on my and avu's forehead giving me a hug.
"Please don't change, have little mercy on us." Riyaz requested.
"We won't." I said giggling.
He did the same and both of them went off.

Pamtech BizTip #42

Dear Leader,
This November ran like Usain Bolt, how come the month is ending in two days time with salaries and bills to pay, yet some hidden desires and dreams are yet to be accomplished. 

Earlier this month, we figured out what we wanted and things we hoped to achieve but the process and risk of bringing desires and dreams to life remained daunting. 

Now we are ending November and starting the ultimate December, we need to restrategise and take risks thoughtfully, cautiously and diligently. 

We need to pay serious attention to what bothers us, listening carefully to our inner voice, It might be telling us something very important for the season. 

We need to overcome negativity, a lot of negative news are flying around, try and ignore those negative feeling. Remain positive against all odds. 

What really makes us hide from actualizing our full potentials? We need to face them this time. Let's confront the obstacles and fears. We either evolve or we die. 

Get to connect with a business community that will support you and your values. I suggest you join the Bedrock Business Community.

Dont forget to pray, seek for the Goodness and Mercy of God. Seek for devine help to manifest your desires. 

Remember, be happy when God blesses your friends in this tough time, don't be jealous else the envy will confuse you and perhaps make you lose focus and track of your own dreams.

Wishing you a fruitful December in advance.

With songs that run the gamut from heartbreaking to satirical and a host of unforgettable film scores, Randy Newman has used his many talents to create musical masterpieces widely recognized by generations of audiences. 

NPR called Newman a “national treasure” in its album review, saying that he “remains first and foremost a craftsman of song, capable of telling ordinary stories in ways no one quite has before,” and the Chicago Tribune said, “Newman is one of the best songwriters of the last half-century … a master of orchestrating mood and playing a range of flawed characters, depicted in mini aural movies compressed into three verses and three minutes.”

Randy Newman’s many honors include seven Grammys, three Emmys, and two Academy Awards, as well as a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame. He was inducted into the Songwriters Hall of Fame in 2002 and the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2013—the same year he was given an Ivor Novello PRS for Music Special International Award. Newman was presented with a PEN New England Song Lyrics of Literary Excellence Award in 2014.(From www.randynewman.com)
